      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_6813749" metaid="metaid_31" name="ALDH1A1 oxidises GA to DGA" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <html:p>Retinal dehydrogenase 1 (ALDH1A1 tetramer) is a cytosolic aldehyde dehydrogenase that can oxidise glyceraldehyde (GA) to D-glycerate (DGA) (Yoval-Sanchez et al. 2013). DGA is a metabolite in a minor pathway of fructose catabolism and serine catabolism.</html:p>
        </notes>
